# VS Code Remote Extension Optimizations for Low-RAM Jetson Nodes
# From: raw refinements.md — Section: Essential Remote Extension Optimizations
# Add to User Settings (settings.json) on Windows 11 host.
# Prevents VS Code background agent (vscode-server) from consuming
# 300-400MB of precious RAM on each 4GB Jetson Nano.

{
  "remote.SSH.defaultExtensions": [],
  "remote.SSH.maxConcurrentConnections": 10,
  "remote.SSH.connectTimeout": 30,
  "extensions.autoUpdate": false
}

# Setting "remote.SSH.defaultExtensions": [] forces VS Code to install
# zero extensions on the Jetson Nanos themselves. All processing remains
# on the Windows 11 host, keeping the Nanos stripped bare for pure
# arithmetic computation.